This tutorial on Responsive Doubles is a BBO movie based on many various sources mainly from ^*IMarty Bergen's Secrets To Winning Bridge - Modern Doubles^*N, from Doubles by Larry Cohen |CP|1|AT|^*Htiny.cc/9epruw^*N|CP||AT|, and from wednesdaygame.com |CP|1|AT|^*Htiny.cc/5cpruw^*N|CP||AT|. Further, Howard Schutzman, BBO nickname "hondo717" our mentor - |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.bridgesights.com/hondobridge/^*N|CP||AT| - had the last words in constructing, shaping, and editing it. For the knowledge I have gained and the help, I am thankful. Please note that this is a basic information and serious students of the game need to review the mentioned sources along with many others.|
PG| ***** 0 ***** |


qx|B, beginning|AT|

According to Marty Bergen Responsive Doubles, ".. are takeout doubles after the opponents bid and raise a suit and partner has bid or doubled. Larry Cohen labels Responsive Double "Cousin of the takeout double. It is used by the takeout doubler's partner." Let us look at a few examples:|
PG| ***** 1 ***** |


NT||
%%% B1 
ST||pn|You,,Partner,|MD|2,,,|sv|o|rh||ah|Responsive Doubles|AH|Board 1|mb|1d|NT|^B@2
West opens one of a suit,|
PG| ***** 2 ***** |


mb|x|an|take out double|at| your partner doubles,|
PG| ***** 3 ***** |


at| and your right hand opponent raises.|MB|2d?|
pg| ***** 4 ***** |


nt|^B@2
Depending on your hand's value and distribution you have several options. First, you are not likely to hold much value in your hand. The opponents probably have 18 to 22 HCP - West opened, Partner doubled and East raised. Nevertheless, at low levels with good distribution you can double (Responsive Double) with values just above 6 to 7 HCP. You need more HCP to double at higher levels.|
pg| ***** 5 ***** |


nt||mb|x|an|Responsive Double|at|^B@2
You probably doubled with a hand as is shown above.|MD|0sqj65hk432d43cQt9,0,0,0|
PG| ***** 6 ***** |


NT|^B@2
With this hand it happened that you hold four cards in both majors. But you can double with only one 4-card major. You know that by a takeout double bid, partner should have at least seven cards in both majors (4-3 or 3-4).|
PG| ***** 7 ***** |


NT|^B@2
So, in this auction you are telling partner "I am too strong to pass, I cannot bid 2N, but wish to play partscore in one of your majors. You get to choose." |
PG| ***** 8 ***** |


NT|^B@2
Let us change your hand a little.|
